         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne  ¶ bot Museum ¶ 14/7/72 ¶  ¶ I was much gratified, rev. and venerable friend, when I received by last mail your kind letter, ¶  and I feel deeply indebted, that you have spared some of your ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.07.14a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Miles Berkeley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Natural History Museum, London, Botany Library, Berkeley correspondence, vol. 9.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">bot Museum</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">14/7/72</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was much gratified, rev. and venerable friend, when I received by last mail your kind letter,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and I feel deeply indebted, that you have spared some of your precious time in the elaboration and remissal of my fungi. I am however grieved to hear of you indisposition, but trust, as your constitution is so strong and good, that you will have shaken off your illness long before this entirely</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The occasions of seeing <name key="Asero%C3%AB">Aseroë</name> in a living state or well preserved occur but very rarely and last of all to one, who is not likely to travel anymore extensively. But if such an occasion should arise, I will watch and examine the species closely.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your workings on the fungi of all parts of the globe are marvellous, and therewith you have stamped your illustrious name for ever on every square mile of the inhabitable world.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am proud of the possession of your autographic photogram for the series of those of illustrious correspondents.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>There is no photograph of Berkeley in M's surviving album at the Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
               </note> My poor picture, made in 1865 (since which time I have not been in an atelier) follows herewith for your kind acceptance.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The <name key="Phallus">Phallus</name> described by me<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The only <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Phallus">Phallus</name>
                     </seg> known to have been described by M, (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">P. vitellinus</seg>) was described in B70.12.03, p. 122.</p>
               </note> was seen only in a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">single</hi>
               </seg> specimen by me, and is placed in Alcohol. I will send it to you in the next case, which is to go to Hooker. As it is an unique sample, it might be desirable to figure it. I will gladly avail myself of your permission to send you any more fungi, which may reach me, or which I may pick up myself</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Trusting that providence will grant you an Humboldtian age<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Humboldt died at the age of 90.</p>
               </note> together with firm health I remain your regardful &amp; grateful </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have now also a <name key="Phallus">Phallus</name> of the section with a reticulate mantle from two widely separated localities, but only one specimen from each.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>One of these localities was the Richmond River, NSW; see M to E. Ramsay, 20 December 1872. See also M to M. Berkeley, 12 February 1872; and M to G. Bentham, 15 July 1872 (in this edition as 72-07-15a). </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Asero%C3%AB">Aseroë</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Phallus">Phallus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
